body:
This implements support for the labeled types (bool, string, counter) in the RLB.

A few interesting bits were carried over from the m-c implementation:

- we have a `ToLabeled` trait that metrics need to implement in order to be "labeled";
- the trait is not exposed outside of the RLB;
- we now have common testing functions;

Note: this was tested in m-c (we're able to use the trait and to call in the RLB type from m-c). The IPC details will require additional thinking but are outside of the scope of the RLB work/this PR.
